meta:
  origin:
    producer: Gapminder and World Bank
    title: US Maternal Mortality and Female Labor Force Participation Index
    description: |-
      The maternal mortality index was calculated by Our World in Data based on maternal mortality data compiled from Gapminder (historical data) and the World Bank (recent data). The original data shows maternal deaths per 100,000 live births.

      The index measures maternal mortality relative to 1900. It was calculated by dividing maternal mortality in each year by maternal mortality in 1900 (so 1900 = 100). Values less than 100 indicate a decrease in maternal mortality relative to 1900; values greater than 100 indicate an increase relative to 1900.
    title_snapshot: US Maternal Mortality and Female Labor Force Participation Index – OWID compilation
    citation_full: OWID calculation based on original data by Gapminder (2010) and the World Bank (2015).
    url_main: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator
    date_accessed: '2017-08-01'
    date_published: '2017'
